The Cape Town Weather Office says another cold front will make landfall in the Peninsula later this week. Capetonians can enjoy warm and pleasant weather conditions until late on Tuesday. Forecaster, Thabisile Ntleko, says temperatures are expected to drop, bringing some rain and cold conditions over large parts of the Western Cape. “Towards Tuesday we are expecting some rain mainly for the Western Cape and Southern parts that’s going to cool temperatures down nicely. And that rain will persist into the Southern and Eastern parts of the province into Wednesday. We should start to see a clearing of that rain towards Thursday evening. “